obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (40925)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title Ordinances.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002&sectionId=40925&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, the Ordinances of every`
  line `Institute may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of the students to the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) the courses of study to be laid down for all degrees and diplomas of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions under which students shall be admitted to the degree or diploma courses and to`
  line `the examinations of the Institute, and shall be eligible for degrees and diplomas;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions of award of the fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions and mode of appointment and duties of examining bodies, examiners and`
  line moderators;
  line
  line `(f) the conduct of examinations;`
  line
  line `(g) the maintenance of discipline among the students of the Institute; and`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which by this Act or the Statutes is to be or may be provided for by the`
  line Ordinances.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (40926)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Ordinances how to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002&sectionId=40926&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, Ordinances shall be`
  line `made by the Senate.`
  line
  line `(2) All Ordinances made by the Senate shall have effect from such date as it may direct, but every`
  line `Ordinance so made shall be submitted, as soon as may be, to the Board and shall be considered by the`
  line `Board at its next meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall have power by resolution to modify or cancel any such Ordinance and such`
  line `Ordinance shall from the date of such resolution stand modified accordingly or cancelled, as the case may`
  line be.
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (40927)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002&sectionId=40927&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) (a) Any dispute arising out of a contract between an Institute and any`
  line `of its employees shall, at the request of the employee concerned or at the instance of the Institute, be referred`
  line `to a Tribunal of Arbitration consisting of one member appointed by the Institute, one member nominated by`
  line `the employee, and an umpire appointed by the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(b) The decision of the Tribunal shall be final and shall not be questioned in any court.`
  line
  line `(c) No suit or proceeding shall lie in any court in respect of any matter, which is required by`
  line `sub-section (1) to be referred to the Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  line
  line `(d) The Tribunal of Arbitration shall have power to regulate its own procedure:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal shall have regard to the principles of natural justice while making such`
  line procedure.
  line
  line `(e) Nothing in any law for the time being in force relating to arbitration shall apply to arbitrations`
  line `under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Any student or candidate for an examination whose name has been removed from the rolls of the`
  line `Institute by the orders or resolution of the Director of the Institute and who has been debarred from`
  line `appearing at the examinations of the Institute for more than one year, may within ten days of the date of`
  line `receipt of such resolution by him, appeal to the Board who may confirm, modify or reverse the decision`
  line `of the Director.`
  line
  line `(3) Any dispute arising out of any disciplinary action taken by the Institute against a student shall, at`
  line `the request of such student, be referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration and the provisions of sub-section (1)`
  line `shall, as far as may be, apply to a reference made under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) Every employee or student of the Institute, notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, have a`
  line `right to appeal within such time as may be laid down by the Statutes, to the Board of Governors against`
  line `the decision of any officer or authority of the Institute, as the case may be, and thereupon the Board may`
  line `confirm, modify or reverse the decision appealed against.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (40928)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Annual report of Director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002&sectionId=40928&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be attached to every statement of accounts laid`
  line `before the Board of each Institute, a report by its Director, with respect to—`
  line
  line `(a) the state of affairs of such Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount, if any, which it proposes to carry forward to any surplus reserves in its balance`
  line sheet;
  line
  line `(c) the extent to which understatement or overstatement of any surplus of income over expenditure or`
  line `any shortfall of expenditure over income has been indicated in the auditor's report and the reasons for such`
  line `understatement or overstatement;`
  line
  line `(d) the productivity of research projects undertaken by the Institute measured in accordance with`
  line `such norms as may be specified by any statutory regulatory authority;`
  line
  line `(e) appointments of the officers and teachers of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(f) benchmark and internal standards set by the Institute, including the nature of innovations in`
  line `teaching, research and application of knowledge.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director shall also be bound to give the complete information and explanation in its report on`
  line `every reservation, qualification or adverse remark contained in the auditors' report.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (40929)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Annual report of each Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002&sectionId=40929&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The annual report of each Institute shall be prepared under`
  line `the direction of the Board, which shall include, among other matters, the steps taken by the Institute`
  line `towards the fulfilment of its objects and an outcome based assessment of the research being undertaken in`
  line `such Institute, and be submitted to the Board on or before such date as may be specified and the Board`
  line `shall consider the report in its annual meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The annual report as approved by the Board shall be published and placed on the website of the`
  line Institute.
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall prepare and release for every year a report, in English and in Hindi, the working`
  line `of the Institute in the previous year on or before the expiry of nine months from the close of financial`
  line `year, and a copy of the same, together with an audited statement of accounts showing the income and`
  line `expenditure for the previous year shall be submitted to the Central Government and the concerned State`
  line `Government within that stipulated time, and the same may be caused to be laid before each House of`
  line `Parliament and the concerned State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (40930)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Co-ordination Forum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002&sectionId=40930&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) In order that there may be better co-ordination among the Institutes,`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, establish, with effect from such date`
  line `as may be specified in the notification, a central body to be called the Co-ordination Forum for all the`
  line `Institutes specified in column (5) of the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The Co-ordination Forum shall consist of the following members, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) the Minister in-charge of the Ministry or Department of the Central Government having`
  line `administrative control of technical education, ex officio, as Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(ii) Secretary to the Government of India, in-charge of the Department of the Central Government`
  line `having administrative control of technical education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iii) four Secretaries in-charge of department looking after Indian Institutes of Information`
  line `Technology of State Governments in which the Institutes are located, to be nominated by the`
  line `Chairperson of the Co-ordination Forum, by rotation for two years, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iv) four Chairpersons of the Institutes, to be nominated by the Chairperson of the Co-ordination`
  line `Forum, by rotation for two years;`
  line
  line `(v) the Directors of each of the Institutes, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vi) four industry partners, to be nominated by the Chairperson of the Co-ordination Forum, not`
  line `more than one from any Institute, by rotation every two years;`
  line
  line `(vii) three persons of eminence, of which at least one shall be a woman, in academia, industry or`
  line `public service, to be nominated by the Co-ordination Forum; and`
  line
  line `(viii) one representative of All India Council of Technical Education:`
  line
  line `Provided that while nominating under clauses (iii), (iv) and (vi), care shall be taken to ensure`
  line `representation of as many Institutes as possible by selecting Secretaries of State Governments,`
  line `Chairpersons of the Institutes, and representatives of industry partners from the Board of different`
  line `Institutes to the extent possible.`
  line
  line `(3) An officer of the Department of Higher Education, Government of India, not below the rank of`
  line `Joint Secretary, concerned with technical education, ex officio, to act as the Member-Secretary of the`
  line `Co-ordination Forum.`
  line
  line `(4) The Co-ordination Forum may, at its discretion, constitute a Standing Committee of the Indian`
  line `Institute of Information Technology Co-ordination Forum (Public-private Partnership) to assist the`
  line `Co-ordination Forum in discharge of its duties and responsibilities.`
  line
  line `(5) The expenditure on the Co-ordination Forum shall be met by the resources pooled by all the`
  line `Institutes governed by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (40931)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Term of office and allowances payable to members of Co-ordination Forum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002&sectionId=40931&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The term`
  line `of office of a member referred to in clause (viii) of sub-section (2) of section 38 shall be three years from`
  line `the date of nomination.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of an ex officio member shall continue so long as the member holds the office`
  line `by virtue of which he is a member.`
  line
  line `(3) While nominating members to the Co-ordination Forum under clauses (iii), (iv) and (vi) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 38, the Chairperson of the Co-ordination Forum shall, to the extent possible, ensure`
  line `maximum possible representation from each Institute.`
  line
  line `(4) The members of the Co-ordination Forum shall be entitled to travelling and such other allowances,`
  line `as may be prescribed, for attending meetings of the Co-ordination Forum or its Committees thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (40932)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Functions and duties of Co-ordination Forum.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002&sectionId=40932&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Co-ordination Forum shall facilitate`
  line `the sharing of experience, ideas and concerns with a view to enhancing the performance of all the`
  line Institutes.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Co-ordination Forum shall perform the`
  line `following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) advise the Central Government to include a new institution or exclude an existing institution`
  line `from the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) deliberate on such matters of common interest to Institutes as may be referred to it by any`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(c) promote necessary co-ordination and co-operation in the working of the Institutes;`
  line
  line `(d) recommend to the Central Government, the institution of scholarships including for research`
  line `and for the benefit of students belonging to the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and other`
  line `socially and educationally backward classes of citizens; and`
  line
  line `(e) perform such other functions as may be referred to it by the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall derogate the powers and functions vested by law in the`
  line `Board or Senate or other authorities of each Institute.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson of the Co-ordination Forum shall ordinarily preside at the meetings of the`
  line `Co-ordination Forum and in the absence, the Secretary to the Government of India, in-charge of the`
  line `Department of the Central Government having administrative control of technical education, shall preside at`
  line `the meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) The Co-ordination Forum shall meet at least once in every year, or as and when deemed`
  line `necessary by the Chairperson of the Co-ordination Forum, and follow such procedure in its meetings, as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (40933)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002&sectionId=40933&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after previous publication, by`
  line `notification make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the form and manner in which the State Government shall submit proposal to the Central`
  line `Government under sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(b) the investment proposal of capital in establishment of the Institute and the respective shares`
  line `under sub-section (7) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) the travelling and other allowances payable to members of the Co-ordination Forum under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 39;`
  line
  line `(d) the procedure to be followed in the meetings of the Co-ordination Forum under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 40.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (40934)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Acts and proceedings not to be invalidated by vacancies, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002&sectionId=40934&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `No act of the Co-ordination`
  line `Forum, or any Institute or Board or Senate or any other body set up under this Act or the Statutes, shall be`
  line `invalid merely by reason of—`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy or defect in the constitution thereof; or`
  line
  line `(b) any irregularity in its procedure not affecting the merits of the case; or`
  line
  line `(c) any defect in the selection, nomination or appointment of a person acting as a member thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (40935)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Returns and information to be provided to Central Government or State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002&sectionId=40935&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The Institute shall furnish to the Central Government such returns or other information with respect to its`
  line `policies or activities as the Central Government may, for the purpose of reporting to Parliament or for the`
  line `making of policy, from time to time require.`
  line
  line `(2) The Institute, shall furnish to the State Government in which such Institute is located, such returns`
  line `or other information with respect to its policies or activities as that Government may, for the purpose of`
  line `reporting to the concerned State Legislature or for the making of policy, from time to time require.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (40936)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002&sectionId=40936&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The Institute shall carry out such directions`
  line `as may be issued to it from time to time by the Central Government for the efficient administration of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (40937)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Institute to be public authority under Right to Information Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002&sectionId=40937&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00033_201723_1517807328002
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the Right`
  line `to Information Act, 2005 (22 of 2005) shall apply to each Institute, as if it were a public authority defined`
  line `in clause (h) of section 2 of the Right to Information Act, 2005.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
